(17600, 'chloramphenicol', 'N/A', 'minor', 'When such drugs are administered to a patient receiving metformin, the patient should be closely observed to maintain adequate glycemic control.In healthy volunteers, the pharmacokinetics of metformin and propranolol and metformin and ibuprofen were not affected when co-administered in single-dose interaction studies.Metformin is negligibly bound to plasma proteins and is, therefore, less likely to interact with highly protein-bound drugs such as salicylates, sulfonamides, chloramphenicol, and probenecid, as compared to the sulfonylureas, which are extensively bound to serum proteins.', 'DailyMed'),
