(19861, 'metformin er  500 mg', 'N/A', 'major', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS Table 3 presents clinically significant drug interactions with metformin hydrochloride extended-release tablets. Table 3: Clinically Significant Drug Interactions with Metformin Hydrochloride Extended-Release Tablets Carbonic Anhydrase Inhibitors Clinical Impact: Carbonic anhydrase inhibitors frequently cause a decrease in serum bicarbonate and induce non-anion gap, hyperchloremic metabolic acidosis. Concomitant use of these drugs with metformin hydrochloride extended-release tablets may increase the risk for lactic acidosis.', 'DailyMed'),
